<section class="section">
  <div class="lede">
    <div class="lede-head">
      <p class="section-num">§ I</p>
      <h2 id="why">Why vendor instead of install</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Skills are markdown plus optional scripts. They are read by Claude Code at session start. Vendoring means committing the skill files to your repository so the capability travels with the project.</p>
  </div>
  <p>The alternative (a global install) is fragile: a teammate clones the repo and the skill is missing.</p>
  <p>The baseline ships skills as committed files. Third-party skills follow the same pattern. Place the skill folder under <code>.claude/skills/&lt;skill-name&gt;/</code>, preserve the original license file, and reference the original source in a top-of-file comment.</p>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="lede">
    <div class="lede-head">
      <p class="section-num">§ II</p>
      <h2 id="example">The {{ baseline.skills.sharedGlobalsWord }} shared globals</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Per <code>CLAUDE.md</code> Appendix B, {{ baseline.skills.sharedGlobalsWord }} baseline skills are vendored from external sources. Each preserves its original license and behavior; the vendoring change is limited to an attribution header and a reference in the constitution's skill index.</p>
  </div>
  <table>
  <thead><tr><th>Skill</th><th>Source</th><th>License</th><th>Role</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td class="phase">claude-automation-recommender</td><td>Anthropic</td><td>Apache 2.0</td><td>Analyzes a codebase and recommends Claude Code automations; used by <code>/init-project</code>.</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="phase">code-structure</td><td>Anthropic</td><td>Apache 2.0</td><td>Mandatory on every code-generation step. Enforces top-down composition and consistent abstraction layers.</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="phase">humanizer</td><td>@blader</td><td>Apache 2.0</td><td>Removes signs of AI-generated writing; invoked unconditionally by <code>prose</code> as its final pass.</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="phase">documentation</td><td>Anthropic</td><td>Apache 2.0</td><td>Reference-doc register (API docs, runbooks, architecture). Conditional invocation from <code>prose</code>.</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="phase">technical-tutorials</td><td>Anthropic</td><td>Apache 2.0</td><td>Tutorial / quickstart / step-by-step register. Conditional invocation from <code>prose</code>.</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="phase">copywriting</td><td>Anthropic</td><td>Apache 2.0</td><td>Persuasive register (landing copy, value props, CTAs). Conditional invocation from <code>prose</code>.</td></tr>
